Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.93,0:00:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,bacteria at one then you see the protozoa the crustaceans the insects you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.31,0:01:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,see the what's that god you know like too much those things you what is that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.20,0:01:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,guy he comes up with his tail like that scorpion 400 million years ago the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.51,0:01:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,scorpion crawled out of the sea I wish he'd stayed there should have stayed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.06,0:01:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there anyway so we have the arachnids the amphibians the fish the octopus it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.92,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was a friend of mine I love octopuses they are so clever and smart and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful I just could just sit and watch octopus they're just they
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.48,0:01:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,slithered and they change the color and nothing you put an octopus on a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.01,0:01:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,checkerboard and he gets checkerboards all over him I mean it's just magical
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.84,0:01:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you take an octopus and put him on a checkerboard he develops checkers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.84,0:01:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out I mean it's just yeah we should put him on an oriental rug see what he does
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.40,0:01:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's a great guy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.59,0:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so here's our buddy the comodo dragon we use him because there are very
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:02:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,prominent people you know influencing all the world who calibrate less than a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,komodo dragon we do not worship life we worship death what is that calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.63,0:02:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean what's that calibrate right right 20 let's say that quote we have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.21,0:02:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,permission through that quote here we worship death not life calibery it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.03,0:02:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,20
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,20. Calibrates less than a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm. Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates less than a Komodo dragon. Oh, wow. The implication
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.00,0:02:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of that is just profound. Less than a reptile. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.16,0:03:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see then, where is the dinosaurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are. Less than a dinosaur. Less than a dinosaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.43,0:03:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people on the planet more dangerous than Tyrannosaurus Rex.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think we should check their passports as they come in? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.28,0:03:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people that go into the cage with the Komodo dragon. There was a movie star's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.28,0:03:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,spouse or friend or something. Went in the cage with the Komodo dragon without shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.31,0:03:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It lived tail to tail. All right. So most of us have a sufficient intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.63,0:03:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that we try to avoid that which is reptilian and predatory. Here you have
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.80,0:03:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the snakes and the alligators, the dinosaurs. Here's the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:04:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, oh, God, I don't want to mention this. The whales and the dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.31,0:04:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who's a whale person, raise your hand. Whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Dolphin people. Dolphins. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's about even. 50-50. They're playing in Pittsburgh next month, the whales versus the dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.95,0:04:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the migratory birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.75,0:04:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't seem to get settled in one place or another. They keep wandering up to there and then back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And birds of prey you'd think would calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.98,0:04:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,lower, but no. 105. Rodents, rhinoceros.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.11,0:04:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Songbirds at only 125. That's a little disappointing, isn't it? I thought, gee, songbirds should be way up higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same with doves. So you see what we project upon them, what we value
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about them. Grizzly bears, water buffaloes. Then we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.72,0:05:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wolves at 190, which people want to put back in the park system.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippopotamuses that you can't trust. I would advise you never
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,trust a hippopotamus. They kill more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.57,0:05:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,people, surprisingly, than any other animal. Isn't that funny? A hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.57,0:05:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we suddenly see, as we do in mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.76,0:05:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at level 200, a shift of intention. At 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.76,0:05:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is rapacious becomes benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.87,0:05:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You go from the carnivore, that which has to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive, to the herbivore, the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.95,0:05:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,grazers, the zebra, the gazelle, the giraffe, the deer, the elk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.95,0:05:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dairy cows, the sheep. And now you see the emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,into the mid-200s of the pets and the gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the gorillas that actually saved the little baby's life. That was really,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that was touching, wasn't it? That wasn't Coco, but
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get what that gorilla was. I got that gorilla in mind. You remember she
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,picked them up, picked up the child and put the child over where,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.88,0:06:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she knew people were coming. We have permission to do that gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That gorilla's consciousness is over 400, 410, 415,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.43,0:06:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,420, 415. Alright, so that gorilla was at about 415
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because of her interaction with humans. And it's more trustable
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.63,0:06:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,than 80% of the people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be with a mountain gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pay attention to your own business, the gorilla pays attention to you and eyes you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and after a while you get used to each other. And as long as you don't eat his bamboo shoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.25,0:07:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he's leaving you a bee. And of course, here's the animals that we love
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and are very unique. And here's, we said the songbird is less there, but the songbird's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,song is 500, just like the cat's purr and the dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we'll go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.56,0:07:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world, I just, we've seen this many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.99,0:07:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to stop? 12, I got 10 minutes to finish up the rest of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world are very interesting because they are the intellectual structure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of democracy and our society, the Western world. You can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the great names of history and you can see their veneration was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.63,0:07:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate. The mid 400s is the stability, the backbone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.63,0:08:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of society, the backbone of government, democracies and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.68,0:08:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we pointed out before, it calibrates I think overall at 455
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.73,0:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or 460, I forget where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.88,0:08:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates I think at 450 or 455 overall. And then if you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.88,0:08:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,remove Marx, Karl Marx jumps to about 460 and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you remove Engels, Engels is at 200, he's not below 200, but he doesn't help the average.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Overall, if you take out Marx and Engels, the calibrated level, the wisdom of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.88,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 460. That's very impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,erudition. Mathematics, science, quantum theory, all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.88,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cover around 460. So 460 you might say is scientific intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,certitude, philosophic discipline,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're following the dialectic, you're respecting the Kantian categories, you're not jumping
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.88,0:09:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from one category to another, which is characteristic of rhetoric.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.88,0:09:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be with logic you have to follow the rules of logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.99,0:09:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the intellectual discipline, the structure, the strength of morality,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,society, government, accountability,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility, and of course the great philosophers looked at man's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.12,0:09:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,upside and looked at man's downside because out of them also came metaphysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.21,0:09:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And theology, and therefore this is the wisdom of the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.21,0:09:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I spent my youth, misspent youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.30,0:09:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kids are out there playing sockball or whatever they were doing there, hitting on each other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in vulgarities. I huddled in a chair with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.34,0:09:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing about being small and fragile is the coach wouldn't allow me to play anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.34,0:09:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't allowed on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.34,0:10:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he said, your bones are going to get crunched out there, Shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.34,0:10:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I lifted heavy books instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all heavy books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, so the thing that you see, life compensates itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't a strong physical mesomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.51,0:10:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so all that energy went elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so these were all the friends of childhood, frankly, the friends of childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we see the great names of all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Copernicus, Darwin, Descartes, Engels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.51,0:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Faraday, all the foundation of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.51,0:10:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.77,0:10:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself had years and years of psychoanalysis every day of the week, an hour on the analyst's couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.77,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not politically correct to favor Freud anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll tell you, if you don't believe in the unconscious, all you have to do is lay on the analyst's couch an hour a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.00,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every week and see what comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.00,0:11:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will rediscover the Oedipal complex, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.00,0:11:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot believe it until you lay down on the couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.54,0:11:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking of a patient that I saw one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I noticed, he was a new patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed that he drove in the exit of the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.61,0:11:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He drove in the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.71,0:11:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when he left, he drove out the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.15,0:11:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And said, help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When he came into the office, you know, we had discussed the psychoanalytic procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.15,0:11:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He laid down on the couch backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.15,0:11:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of his head being here and his feet there, he lay around this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.15,0:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.29,0:11:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So 50 years of listening to the inner, speaks to the human mind, you know, year after year after year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Having gone through it yourself gives you a certain insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.29,0:11:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So when critics come around, I say, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.29,0:12:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.29,0:12:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You just lay down there and see what comes up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are my friends, Plato and Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, my favorite friend is Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.42,0:12:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you put together what we said this morning about the intrinsic innocence of mankind, you know, Socrates said that all men can choose only the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.90,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that really reinforces, you know, you may not be able to go along with Jesus Christ and forgive your persecutors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But Socrates certainly makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you understand what Socrates says, then you can apply what Jesus recommended, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Buddha recommended forgiveness because they don't know what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion out of man's ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.90,0:12:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said the only limitation in man is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.90,0:12:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Which Jesus Christ said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.74,0:12:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was Socrates that explained it and made it operational.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.74,0:12:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it also satisfies your intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That man's motivation, he can only choose what he perceives to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.92,0:13:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So if the good is killing off Americans, he's doing the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.92,0:13:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The more Americans he kills and blows up, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The more Americans he blows up, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.65,0:13:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he believe in forgiveness?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.45,0:13:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he believes in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.87,0:13:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we forgive somebody who's pledged to the death of all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.40,0:13:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't one person in this room he would save.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.91,0:13:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,None of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.98,0:13:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.33,0:13:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you should die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we forgive him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He believes that's the ultimate good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.27,0:14:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's doing the ultimate good with the god of his imagination or his belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So in his naivete, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,His naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, that which is extremely naive is extremely dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.03,0:14:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A ten-year-old behind the wheel of a car, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.09,0:14:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No sense of responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.09,0:14:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody for the lives or the welfare of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.37,0:14:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean to turn your back on them when they're holding a loaded gun, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To turn your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.75,0:14:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it means to stand up for what you believe to be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To stand up for what you believe to be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.75,0:14:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.91,0:14:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.85,0:14:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what time we got to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, 35 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm trying to finish up a couple thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.85,0:14:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.98,0:14:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:15:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.77,0:15:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.77,0:15:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.61,0:15:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We say that potentiality becomes an actuality when conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.61,0:15:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.61,0:15:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this infinite field is what gives your thoughts power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.61,0:15:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.09,0:15:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In Scotland, in the middle of the tattoos, I'm thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to have my group experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last I thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing I know, a couple weeks ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.61,0:15:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, hey, let's get Piper's so we get the experiential instead of just the mental, intellectual, theoretical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thought, a couple years ago in Scotland, bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.61,0:15:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,happened this morning. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:15:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That is causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.61,0:15:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just because you love that thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the thought, one day, you're sitting down and I'll say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.71,0:16:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,geez, why don't we get the bangpipers that we're going to get for St. Andrews
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.71,0:16:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and have them come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because not everybody's going to be going to St. Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we get to experience the experiential, what 525 or what 530 feels like.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.79,0:16:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What 530 feels like.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.79,0:16:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That oneness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Our oneness with our fellow man through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have trouble forgiving somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.79,0:16:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We hold Socrates that each person is choosing what in their perception is the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.32,0:16:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then within our heart, we hold a compassion for that person's ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just seeing their ignorance but having compassion for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that that person probably completely believes what he's saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which brings forth even more compassion because I realize the helplessness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brainwash of that kind of a person
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.91,0:17:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,who's now unable to think independently or for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.99,0:17:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.56,0:17:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.56,0:17:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.56,0:17:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the situation we say that things manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So if there weren't any bangpipers around in Arizona,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.60,0:17:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't have had them this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.60,0:17:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.60,0:17:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.16,0:17:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.16,0:17:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So intention then is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of intention, what is held in mind is the Empire State Building appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.16,0:17:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The bangpipers show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us are here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The charts get done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.25,0:17:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The books get written.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.25,0:17:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all because of collective intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I want to thank everyone here for energizing our collective intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.25,0:17:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which I enjoyed very much this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.25,0:18:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see you again after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.25,0:18:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us a story about the Mitchell Gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to fight your way up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.72,0:18:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Richie Mitchell's gym when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.83,0:18:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the former medium heavyweight champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.13,0:18:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always getting beaten up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was brought up not to hit people lower than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people weren't brought up that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was hittable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially during corner practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:18:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I belong to the church choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday and Sunday we practiced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.02,0:19:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy solo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.02,0:19:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy soloist, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.02,0:19:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.31,0:19:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I sang the Obligato de Panis Angelicus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.31,0:19:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A full cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A full orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Stained glass windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.51,0:19:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun coming back and lighting up the incense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And this incredible voice floated out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Physicality was here, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.51,0:19:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but anyway, I used to get beaten up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.51,0:19:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.51,0:19:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried being nice to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.51,0:19:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.51,0:19:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I went to Richie Mitchell's gym and I learned the Marquis of Queensbury rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.51,0:19:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, so we boxed with Marquis of Queensbury rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.51,0:19:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wasn't a heavy hitter, but I was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I found that if you give a guy a bloody nose, that's usually the end of the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would give him a bloody nose and the guy would go like this and the fight was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So they started leaving me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.05,0:20:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.05,0:20:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I visited my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She lived in a different neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.07,0:20:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Went out in the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.07,0:20:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was challenged to a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.07,0:20:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I never turned down a challenge to a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.07,0:20:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.24,0:20:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I was gonna lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.24,0:20:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured, what the hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.24,0:20:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went out and scrapped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So this guy challenges me to a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And he kicked me in the butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.24,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, where.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was down on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.24,0:20:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So I learned to never use Marquis of Queensbury rules in other areas of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.33,0:20:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.33,0:20:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.33,0:20:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you know, you're the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.33,0:20:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.33,0:20:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.33,0:20:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,down the ground. So I learned never use Marquis of Queensbury rules in other
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,areas of the world, which is what our country is learning. Yeah, Marquis of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.70,0:20:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Queensbury rules are okay. Anyway, then I, when I was in the Navy, I went aboard a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.33,0:20:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,minesweeper, and the boatswain's mate there, who stayed a friend of mine until
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:21:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he left this world not too long ago, he said, Shorty, do you box? I said, well I
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,took boxing lessons. So he said, we'll go up in the gun tub. Okay. So we went up in the gun tub to go around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He hit me once and I was out cold. Then I find out later he was the champion of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.11,0:21:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the third fleet. Jimmy Sanders, God bless him. We stayed in touch. 18 guys on that ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.78,0:21:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened the last
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.88,0:21:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,one, the Survivor. Christmas, you don't get any more Christmas cards. So all the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.67,0:21:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,non-smokers are dead. That's true. All my buddies who were, they always ate out of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.41,0:22:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the brown paper bag, and they died jogging, actually. That's a fact, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.91,0:22:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll get back to reality here now. We were talking about traps, traps. The
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.95,0:22:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reason we're always looking for something outside of ourself is because
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.47,0:22:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we feel insufficient. If you go from incomplete to complete, that's the way
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you picture the world, then at any moment you're incomplete. Because you project
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.18,0:22:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself ahead in time, and you're going to be incomplete. You may not be incomplete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.18,0:22:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,now, but five minutes from now you can be incomplete. So how do you stay
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.78,0:22:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,incomplete? Well, at this exact moment, everybody here is complete. Agree? Anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.36,0:22:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,lacking anything? I don't know. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.75,0:22:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you go from, instead from incomplete to complete, at every moment
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.05,0:22:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you are complete. The way to get away from all anxiety is to live in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.88,0:23:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this exact split second of now, this mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.11,0:23:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you're going to be beheaded, okay? Right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.56,0:23:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,do I have a problem? No. Now do I have a problem? No. Now do I have a problem? No!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.73,0:23:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just put your head on the block,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.56,0:23:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,do I have a problem now? no.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have a problem now? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.38,0:23:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have a problem now? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.46,0:23:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at your head. Do you have a problem now? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.15,0:23:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At any one moment of time, you do not have a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.50,0:23:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're not projecting into the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.85,0:23:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're living in the real, the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.09,0:23:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the real, the experiential, you're always complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.72,0:23:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is perfect this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.77,0:24:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You might have to go to the bathroom five minutes from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.68,0:24:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but now you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.90,0:24:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.96,0:24:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We were going to talk about something important today,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.90,0:24:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't remember what it was now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.20,0:24:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.66,0:24:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.47,0:24:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The other trap is the reason people don't get out of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.06,0:24:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.66,0:24:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What holds the ego in place is that we get, we juice it, we juice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.75,0:24:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.84,0:24:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't people give up hate?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.19,0:24:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they get so much out of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.26,0:24:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They juice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.21,0:24:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.71,0:24:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They love hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a recent semi-celebrity, all of the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.69,0:24:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and as she got arrested, she was just radiating with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.23,0:24:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Blissful glee as she's being arrested, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.71,0:24:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.54,0:25:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens is, you see, because of the spiritual energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.55,0:25:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it hasn't arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.05,0:25:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual energy doesn't arise until consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.59,0:25:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll show the brain physiology shift at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.66,0:25:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a brain physiology shift at that level?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.05,0:25:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.09,0:25:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so the ego lives on animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.43,0:25:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I need that brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.02,0:25:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You got the next?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.99,0:25:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.06,0:25:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the animal is left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.01,0:25:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It always has to be ready to get what's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.06,0:25:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It lives off adrenaline, danger, and et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.74,0:25:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Its source is animal energy, the thrill of hate, the thrill of anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.64,0:25:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the thrill of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.64,0:25:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things pump out adrenaline and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.79,0:26:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and neurotransmitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.07,0:26:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this the one we wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.38,0:26:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.68,0:26:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.33,0:26:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go back to quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.77,0:26:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We can live without quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.35,0:26:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.09,0:26:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here we got quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.38,0:26:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't want quantum mechanics now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.55,0:26:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If I couldn't have it when I didn't want it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.72,0:26:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.68,0:26:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we get hooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.25,0:26:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We get hooked on this pathway here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.93,0:26:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.50,0:26:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought it was subliminal, but I was faster than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.36,0:26:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm faster than 110,000th of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.68,0:26:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.59,0:26:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.75,0:26:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We call it in the human left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.64,0:26:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an instinctual animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.38,0:26:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And people who live below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.81,0:27:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the only source of psychic energy they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.83,0:27:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.51,0:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they have to have it and thrive on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.07,0:27:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take hatred and self-pity and all that away from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.36,0:27:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here who's a therapist
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.02,0:27:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,knows that people that are hooked on self-pity,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.10,0:27:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.10,0:27:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When they're hooked on being victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.78,0:27:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no way you can cure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.77,0:27:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The payoff of being victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.48,0:27:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,self-pity, anger, resentment, being right,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.11,0:27:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, it's overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.22,0:27:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like intoxicating.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.26,0:27:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is, I'm right, you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.78,0:27:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.33,0:27:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens at level 200 now
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.31,0:27:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have the inflow of kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.72,0:27:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.03,0:27:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish it had a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.27,0:27:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kundalini sounds so Sanskrit like it came from Uhu land.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.42,0:27:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.92,0:27:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for lack of a better word,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.88,0:27:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.79,0:27:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a different new energy now begins to pour in.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.55,0:27:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we see the difference at level 200
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.68,0:27:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in both the human and the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.54,0:28:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the beginning of spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.79,0:28:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.61,0:28:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.03,0:28:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.01,0:28:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.07,0:28:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're unaware of your is-ness and beingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.38,0:28:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.13,0:28:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you do not value the life of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.80,0:28:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Few below 200 do not value the life of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.54,0:28:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The life of others is meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.79,0:28:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler says they lost the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.98,0:28:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,kill all the Germans,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.96,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,burn down, you know, burn down Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.79,0:28:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,slaughter the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.75,0:28:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be seeing that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.79,0:28:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the international trial coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.92,0:28:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Slaughter the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.33,0:28:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,slaughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.66,0:28:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,slaughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.00,0:28:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or as in-laws, slaughter his own children, slaughter his people, slaughter his own troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.19,0:28:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.69,0:28:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Level 200 or under, others don't have any worth or humanist value to their existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,other than being utilizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.03,0:29:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No conscious awareness of the worth or the value of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.66,0:29:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, to expect that being a decent person, they will respect you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.94,0:29:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're projecting that value onto them and presuming they have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.83,0:29:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.19,0:29:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.26,0:29:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What calls for mercy is an idiot's call to them, and they'll chuck your head right off.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.52,0:29:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As you cry for mercy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.97,0:29:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it has no reality below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.75,0:29:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when you get to 200 that the value of others, others even, comes into the consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.79,0:29:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what happens then?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.27,0:29:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see, the shift in the brain function is now right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.60,0:29:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this is a fast brain to the emotional reaction that reacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.86,0:29:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill the bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.02,0:29:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.86,0:29:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember him as the son of a bitch who deserved to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.19,0:29:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the left brain view of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.05,0:30:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get the right brain, the fast track is to the prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.57,0:30:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but what you see here is the birth of the etheric energy body.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.59,0:30:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only at 200 that you develop an energy field body.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the etheric body and the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.92,0:30:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now information fast tracks the etheric brain, and you get the essence of the thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.85,0:30:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and that makes you hold back from pulling the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.94,0:30:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't pull the trigger unless you've got to pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.24,0:30:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas in the left brain, you're happy to pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.01,0:30:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you're eager for an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.85,0:30:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we have completely two different populations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.31,0:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, here we have left brain dominance, which is linear, based on stress, fight or flight,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.44,0:30:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,alarm reaction, thymic stress, disrupts the acupuncture system, and proneness of the disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.33,0:30:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, you see right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.92,0:30:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're picking up right brain is the overall dimension, the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.21,0:31:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You release endorphins, positive emotions that supports the thymus gland,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.71,0:31:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which pours out more killer cells, decreases immunity, increases healing,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.48,0:31:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and you attract.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.59,0:31:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotions is slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.32,0:31:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the difference in therapeutic results between the healer and the, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.28,0:31:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,academically limited treater, you know, the provider of services.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.65,0:31:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they call it provider of services, and you're a consumer of services.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.25,0:31:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the provider-consumer, which is the business model, has a certain level of recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.04,0:31:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I discovered from the clinic back east where I had, you know, 50 employees,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.43,0:31:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a dozen therapists, and psychiatrists, psychologists, social workers,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.43,0:31:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is some got terrific results all the time, and some got lousy results all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.93,0:31:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.43,0:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they were all academically well-trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.46,0:32:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was two different doctors having different results?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.46,0:32:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because of the calibration level of the physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.51,0:32:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the double-blind experiment, therefore, is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.51,0:32:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's usually set up fallaciously, with skepticism, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.90,0:32:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it discounts the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.00,0:32:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It discounts the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.00,0:32:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's who the treater is, who the healer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.00,0:32:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes all the difference in the world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.00,0:32:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they get in my mind, this SLB is going to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.22,0:32:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By God, he's going to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.66,0:32:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, I stayed in practice long after I closed my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.66,0:32:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a part-time just Thursday morning as they saw some guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.66,0:32:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because they'd been with me so many years, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.66,0:32:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the positive transference was keeping them going.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.66,0:32:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I knew if I quit on them, they'd croak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.66,0:32:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, I've got to wait until they all die before I can quit, which I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.70,0:32:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Including the guy who used to walk in and ask me for a light when he had his oxygen thing on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.22,0:33:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd smoke a cigarette with his oxygen thing on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.22,0:33:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, can you do that? Won't we blow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.22,0:33:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, no, he won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.22,0:33:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.29,0:33:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He must know, or he would have blown himself away already.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.68,0:33:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the dedication to this guy, you know, there's a dedication to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.85,0:33:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was that love for your patient, your love for who they are, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.85,0:33:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't help but recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.85,0:33:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was only one patient I treated that didn't recover, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.85,0:33:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why to this day, and I knocked my brains out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.30,0:33:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything holistic, everything you could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.56,0:33:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And he just would not get well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.92,0:33:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'll have to kill this guy, let's get rid of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.01,0:33:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.01,0:33:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, and he told me he had one day of happiness in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.01,0:33:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At age 26, he never forgot that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.01,0:34:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he lived in the hope that that day would recur somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.61,0:34:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.61,0:34:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.88,0:34:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent him to the Mayo Clinic, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.88,0:34:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So when local conditions are right, one local affecting condition is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.00,0:34:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are sort of heavy karmic situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.03,0:34:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In which the permission, you haven't achieved the right or the permission yet, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's just go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.44,0:34:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What we were going to do was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.44,0:34:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the, I wanted to just bring in the Heisenberg principle, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.96,0:34:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the quantum mechanics and the kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.96,0:34:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, you're all familiar with the Schrodinger equations and the Dirac equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.96,0:34:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the von Neumann process.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.96,0:34:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is by which the Heisenberg principle operates.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.96,0:34:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.96,0:35:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayne Dyer's book, Power of Intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.25,0:35:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the local conditions is intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.25,0:35:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So your intention about that person, the way you hold them in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.25,0:35:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is already very powerfully influencing the consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.25,0:35:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the physics experiments where the result is altered
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.25,0:35:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by the mere observation of the experimenter,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.25,0:35:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,does not take into account the consciousness level of the experimenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.34,0:35:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say the average experimenter is around 420 or 430, around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.34,0:35:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looks at the experiment with a certain expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.57,0:35:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequence has already changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.92,0:35:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's collapsed the wave function and brought about a potentiality into an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.92,0:35:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be the effect of somebody who calibrated 500 meters?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.92,0:35:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated 500 looking at that experiment with a specific intention in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.92,0:36:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the value of the teacher, the healer, the therapist, the coach, the confidant.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.13,0:36:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you're holding in mind for those people now has quite a powerful effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.13,0:36:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the likelihood of their fulfilling your expectation for them is quite high.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.30,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the von Neumann, I mean the Heisenberg process then,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.30,0:36:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is the explanation in quantum mechanics of the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.30,0:36:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The field in which you're operating.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.30,0:36:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's leave that, it's the same sort of academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.30,0:36:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just want to show that you can move from the intellectual, scientific,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.30,0:36:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and move through the higher mathematics, move into quantum theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.34,0:36:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and merge into the next paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.34,0:36:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at level 500, you leave the world of academic Newtonian,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.36,0:36:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave via the door of quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.36,0:36:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and still stay a respectable scientific person.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.36,0:37:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they say, are you spiritual?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.46,0:37:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, no, I'm just practicing the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.46,0:37:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just practicing that, applying the Heisenberg principle to experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.98,0:37:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to see this, it's too academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.38,0:37:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And, alright, so we're again talking about causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.38,0:37:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.38,0:37:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no cause outside of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.15,0:37:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only what you hold in mind that has any power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.15,0:37:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only subject to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.15,0:37:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.15,0:37:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.15,0:37:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, people think that, well, the source of happiness is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.42,0:37:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, if the source of happiness is out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.42,0:37:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then now you're a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.42,0:37:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.42,0:37:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're subject to fear and anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.48,0:37:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the out there-ness can disappear at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.48,0:37:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, whatever you achieve in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.28,0:37:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as you will see,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.28,0:37:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is not related to out there-ness at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.28,0:38:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, statistically, it has nothing to do with out there-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.63,0:38:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Statistically, the rate of happiness is directly a result of level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.63,0:38:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you see the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.63,0:38:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness is practically zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.46,0:38:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All the way down here, the rate of happiness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.46,0:38:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we're still less than ten percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.46,0:38:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And anger, which people love to be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.61,0:38:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.61,0:38:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the animal in you loves to puff up and intimidate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.61,0:38:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get a false sense of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.61,0:38:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,False sense of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.01,0:38:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride, which is as far as you can go, below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.32,0:38:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly feels better than these things below it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.32,0:38:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't knock pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.32,0:38:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.32,0:38:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's very, very vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.32,0:38:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you cross over the line at 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.44,0:38:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the rate of happiness jumps 22 to 55,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.44,0:39:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it escalates rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.44,0:39:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, happiness is related to the level of consciousness directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.48,0:39:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Directly related to the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.48,0:39:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you plan to live in the moment and stop anticipating the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.53,0:39:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave the future up to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.67,0:39:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can feel fine as it cuts your head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.67,0:39:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do a good job of it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.73,0:39:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps the tip of my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.73,0:39:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a few ducats for you, my boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.09,0:39:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, don't tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.25,0:39:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tip the has-been.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.34,0:39:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who remember some previous lives will remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.34,0:39:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always well to pay the has-been, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.34,0:39:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move to the next one, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.69,0:39:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.48,0:39:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we know what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.96,0:39:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. Is that what we were going to go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.96,0:39:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.96,0:40:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.82,0:40:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We did brain function, rate of happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.01,0:40:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.01,0:40:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.53,0:40:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.53,0:40:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, today we're talking about the traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.53,0:40:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about the seductions, the payoffs of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.94,0:40:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you never have to give up the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.46,0:40:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You never have to give up greed and all those things
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.46,0:40:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that you think you can possibly never give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.46,0:40:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to give up is one thing over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.46,0:40:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what it is, the negative feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.78,0:40:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the out-there-ness, there's only one thing you've got to be willing to surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.51,0:40:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the payoff of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.51,0:40:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the fun of cutting off somebody's head
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.88,0:40:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as the fun of getting a new car.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.17,0:40:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always just the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.17,0:40:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I surrender the pleasure I get out of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.17,0:40:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.17,0:41:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, can I give up the feeling of satisfaction I get out of there?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.17,0:41:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.69,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the question is, well, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.69,0:41:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be willing to give up the payoff of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.69,0:41:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.69,0:41:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.69,0:41:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.69,0:41:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up being better than other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.69,0:41:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.69,0:41:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.09,0:41:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what you want to get rid of and just see that there's a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.09,0:41:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's only one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.09,0:41:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like Johnny One Note.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.32,0:41:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the payoff of it, not the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.32,0:41:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're addicted to is the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.84,0:41:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's getting even.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.09,0:41:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.09,0:41:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.44,0:41:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.44,0:41:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.44,0:41:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You are so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.69,0:41:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure of being arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.69,0:41:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that I am better than other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.17,0:41:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people give it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.94,0:41:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My view of the world is right and yours is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.94,0:41:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.11,0:41:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.11,0:42:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All those positionalities, there's only one thing holding them all in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.11,0:42:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They have exactly the same single payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.50,0:42:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the ego juice you get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.50,0:42:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over again, all you've got to do is be willing to give up the ego juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.65,0:42:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That person says, well, I can't give up the ego juice out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.65,0:42:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I hold a gun to their head and I say, if you don't, I'm going to blow your freaking brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.65,0:42:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.65,0:42:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.65,0:42:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.71,0:42:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.71,0:42:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.71,0:42:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Revolver to your brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.13,0:42:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you give up the juice of being right all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.13,0:42:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.05,0:42:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That was, I had it on an empty cylinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.38,0:42:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But he gave it up right then and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.38,0:42:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.46,0:42:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So consequently, it's a matter of willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.57,0:42:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, will is a whole different thing than being addicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.57,0:42:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.57,0:43:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the human will is only as strong as one's level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.59,0:43:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll hear people say, I tried willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.59,0:43:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.59,0:43:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.59,0:43:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody at consciousness level 150, that's the power of their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.88,0:43:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they use willpower, it only, it calibrates at 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.26,0:43:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't strong enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.26,0:43:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A lifetime of doing this, it's going to take more than 150, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.26,0:43:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We know all the good intentions that went by the board January 1st things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.36,0:43:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do this this year and it doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.36,0:43:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.65,0:43:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.65,0:43:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see that I of myself am unable to do this, you ask for God's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.19,0:43:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the spiritual will calibrates at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.19,0:43:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.19,0:43:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine will is a 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.44,0:44:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The divine will, then recovery from a lifetime addiction, can happen in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.25,0:44:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are members of 12-step groups were helplessly, hopelessly addicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.25,0:44:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I treated so many over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.25,0:44:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the instant they completely surrendered to God, they recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.25,0:44:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant, they recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.25,0:44:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes as a flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.25,0:44:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way out of anything, any stuckness, then, is to see that it isn't you couldn't, but you wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.94,0:44:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't because in your experience, willpower hasn't worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.01,0:44:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, surrender at great depth brings recovery from anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.01,0:44:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender at great depth, yeah, is the secret, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.23,0:44:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.78,0:45:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about traps and we mentioned sort of far out kinds of religious and spiritual fantasy worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.26,0:45:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fiction, fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.26,0:45:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And people get hooked in that fiction because the child in them, you know, likes the idea of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.26,0:45:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Likes the idea of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.48,0:45:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Potter books are honest because she tells you that it's fiction and that it's magic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.48,0:45:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't pretend that this is a spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.48,0:45:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't pretend it's a spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.48,0:45:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Her books calibrate, I forget, to 10 or 20 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.57,0:45:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when they came out, a lot of people, evangelicals especially, were worried about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.57,0:45:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does calibrate over 200 because she makes clear that which is fiction and that which is fact
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.57,0:45:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is deleterious mixes the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.57,0:45:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're reading fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.57,0:45:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's expressed as though it's fact, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.57,0:45:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So research uncovered these secrets hidden in the hairs of the camel, the nose of the camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.61,0:45:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And God really revealed his secrets there, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.61,0:46:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You count the stones of the Sphinx and divide it by the sacred cubit and all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.76,0:46:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So to avoid that, to avoid the traps of that, all you need is to compare it to that which is highly integrative.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.40,0:46:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That which calibrates at the very highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.40,0:46:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the earmarks then of spiritual truth and teachers and spiritual groups?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.75,0:46:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing about spiritual truth is it's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.46,0:46:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence within.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.46,0:46:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When the ego drops, when the ego dissolves, which it did when you turn over your...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.82,0:46:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing left was life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.86,0:46:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.30,0:46:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego turning over one's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.94,0:46:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you think is your life is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.94,0:46:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's the core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.94,0:47:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego has you convinced that it is the source of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.19,0:47:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when you're faced with the last thing left to go through the last door is to turn over your life to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.57,0:47:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,then it takes all what you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.57,0:47:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you've heard the truth before, the vibrations and the frequency of your aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.57,0:47:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And from Zen I got,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.67,0:47:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.67,0:47:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you walk through the final door of fear and it is terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.67,0:47:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You are dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.67,0:47:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually feel yourself die.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.67,0:47:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then shines forth the splendor of all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.67,0:47:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.94,0:47:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the truth is true at all times and in all places.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.44,0:47:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of that state and that condition has been the same throughout time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.82,0:47:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's the Buddha, whether it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.21,0:47:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All the mystics throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.21,0:47:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of the Self with a capital S as God immanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.21,0:48:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, religion is preoccupied with God transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.40,0:48:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That means elsewhere in time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.40,0:48:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mystic is concerned with the realization of God as immanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.46,0:48:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is divine is obviously everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.46,0:48:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be just transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.46,0:48:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If that was so, God would come up and stop right around here, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.46,0:48:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is you would be outside of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.46,0:48:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, if God is universal, then God is within you as well, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.46,0:48:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If God is the source of all life, then the source of your life also.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.78,0:48:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The radiance of divinity within, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.86,0:48:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What it does is it silences the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.05,0:48:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It silences the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.32,0:48:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.32,0:48:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind never talks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.21,0:48:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.69,0:48:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversing this is an aspect of the persona
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.69,0:48:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an attribute that you learn later.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.69,0:48:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like with the whereabouts of the body and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.69,0:49:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And people are talking to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.69,0:49:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't figure out who the hell they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.69,0:49:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is you, there is no such thing as that in that bodiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.69,0:49:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see that they presume the body must be where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.71,0:49:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So you learn how to correspond.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.71,0:49:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And after a great deal of time, then there's the relearning of how to be in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.71,0:49:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And if one is karmically destined,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.71,0:49:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then that is what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.71,0:49:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You do come back in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.71,0:49:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world calls back in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.57,0:49:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the truth is the truth at all times and all places.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.57,0:49:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So described 5000 B.C. in the Gita in the great Aryan.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.57,0:49:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was first described about 5000 B.C. out of the Aryan culture of ancient Hindu.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.57,0:49:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient India.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.57,0:49:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And has remained the same ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.57,0:49:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.13,0:49:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.96,0:50:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.11,0:50:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's free and available to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.11,0:50:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Available, open to all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.11,0:50:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.11,0:50:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to sign up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.11,0:50:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.88,0:50:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.88,0:50:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.88,0:50:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing peddled.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.88,0:50:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No magical formulas or mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.88,0:50:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be a mystery to that which is universally true?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.53,0:50:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient hidden mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.53,0:50:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.53,0:50:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.53,0:50:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.53,0:50:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For 5000 B.C. you could be a master.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.53,0:50:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.53,0:50:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Make me a master, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.28,0:50:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With kinesiology you can tell the truth of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.28,0:50:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no hidden secrets in this universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.28,0:50:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.38,0:50:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.38,0:50:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even without kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.01,0:50:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to leave the body, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.03,0:50:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Which I learned to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.03,0:50:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.03,0:50:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I learned how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.03,0:50:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It will.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.03,0:50:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know the secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.32,0:50:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in that box?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.32,0:50:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just project yourself into the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.32,0:50:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.32,0:51:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.32,0:51:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You come back out of the box and tell people it says, hello, greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.32,0:51:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Say hello to everyone who says, hello, greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.32,0:51:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no hidden secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.26,0:51:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.26,0:51:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.26,0:51:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available to everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.26,0:51:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to make it available in all kinds of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.26,0:51:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.26,0:51:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to gain or lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.26,0:51:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonsectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.26,0:51:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not the exposition of a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.42,0:51:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See how people own God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.90,0:51:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God favors this genetic group.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.90,0:51:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God favors this part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.90,0:51:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God has favoritism.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.90,0:51:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what kind of an anthropomorphic God that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.90,0:51:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is available to all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.28,0:51:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.28,0:51:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.28,0:51:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.28,0:51:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth has nothing to gain or lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.26,0:51:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you go with it or don't go with it is immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.07,0:52:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.86,0:52:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy says, I don't believe him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.86,0:52:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, don't read the freaking book.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.86,0:52:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.86,0:52:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me a favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.86,0:52:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.90,0:52:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what gain is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.90,0:52:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What gain is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.90,0:52:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's devoid of positionalities and it's independent of opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.90,0:52:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.90,0:52:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.90,0:52:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the things that we're talking about that are misleading, the fabrications about spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.00,0:52:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all have to do with linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.00,0:52:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.00,0:52:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Time, place, people with names.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.00,0:52:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.26,0:52:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.26,0:52:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.57,0:52:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.57,0:52:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.28,0:52:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.28,0:52:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.28,0:52:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.28,0:52:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.28,0:52:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.40,0:52:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.40,0:52:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.40,0:52:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.40,0:52:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.40,0:52:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.40,0:52:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.65,0:52:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Dinggong, from the year 6032, and planet number 67.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.01,0:52:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.38,0:52:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence within is like infinite space.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.13,0:52:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.51,0:52:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.38,0:53:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is like an infinite field of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.03,0:53:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,An infinite field of energy is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.59,0:53:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any thingness, dates, positions, form, figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.78,0:53:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.78,0:53:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.78,0:53:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It can brush its teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.78,0:53:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It can make it thats.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.13,0:53:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no thingness to it, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.76,0:53:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Devoid of positionality, truth is not anti-anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.80,0:53:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood and ignorance are not its enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.09,0:53:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but merely represents the absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.80,0:53:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the dictum, there is no opposite to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.90,0:53:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only its absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.26,0:53:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth has no opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.78,0:53:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It only has an absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.80,0:53:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's comparable to electricity being in a wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.73,0:53:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The electricity is either there or not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.61,0:53:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's not there, you can't say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.46,0:53:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,well, now what's running down the wire is offness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.84,0:53:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and offness is the opposite of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.80,0:53:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.53,0:53:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.76,0:54:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it doesn't have an enemy, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.28,0:54:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's either there or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.88,0:54:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no requirements or demands,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.15,0:54:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no required memberships, you don't have to sign up,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.80,0:54:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have any dues, no oaths, no pledges,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.17,0:54:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no regulations, no rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.59,0:54:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.53,0:54:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because those are methods of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.46,0:54:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why would somebody who's enlightened want to control you?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.23,0:54:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he'd get out of controlling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.40,0:54:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, your sex life, what you eat, where you sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.44,0:54:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you should work, take this job, not that job.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.11,0:54:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you'll see those things which are really sort of cults.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.82,0:54:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They worship this guy, usually with some fancy name,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.05,0:54:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he tells them all about their sex life, what to wear, how to dress,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.75,0:54:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.30,0:54:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All for a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.01,0:54:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, no regulations, no oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.21,0:54:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to sign anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.80,0:55:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no consequences if you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.57,0:55:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.09,0:55:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave any time you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.78,0:55:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.92,0:55:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to put a rattlesnake in your mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.63,0:55:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-controlling.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.80,0:55:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual purity has no interest in the personal lives of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.71,0:55:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why would an enlightened being be interested in what you wear,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.84,0:55:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your dress, your style, your sex life, your economics,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.65,0:55:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your family patterns, your dietary habits,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.19,0:55:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether you wear a hat or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.17,0:55:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you wear a hat or a beard,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.28,0:55:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,various other anatomical details, what you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.90,0:55:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.40,0:55:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual truth is free of force or intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.90,0:55:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No brainwashing, no adulation of leaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.53,0:55:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,no training rituals, no indoctrinations,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.05,0:55:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.05,0:55:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A young man came on TV, I think it was last night or the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.67,0:56:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He follows a sort of highly visible leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.40,0:56:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And as he began to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.82,0:56:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he was just like the perfect exposition of brainwashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.44,0:56:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The languaging, the style, the context in which he held it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.36,0:56:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just perfect brainwash.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.03,0:56:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've heard brainwash,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.73,0:56:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it looks like and what it sounds like.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.65,0:56:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can spot brainwash.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.19,0:56:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mile away.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.19,0:56:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a kid who'd been indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.71,0:56:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All his, the style of the languaging,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.38,0:56:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from his background, ethnic, educational,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.67,0:56:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that isn't his style of languaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.86,0:56:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an indoctrinated style of languaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.86,0:56:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The style of languaging is foreign to the person's cultural background
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.46,0:56:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and educational level, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.86,0:56:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.30,0:56:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing we go is non-binding.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.23,0:56:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no regulations, laws, edicts, contracts, or pledges.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.90,0:57:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, those are all attempts to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.03,0:57:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would that which is infinite and present in all that exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.30,0:57:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, be willing to control you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.86,0:57:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Willing to control you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.07,0:57:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that's coming from a linearity and a causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.86,0:57:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand, as we've explained before,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.84,0:57:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite field of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.01,0:57:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a giant electromagnetic field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.13,0:57:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And your spirit, by virtue of your freedom of your will,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.15,0:57:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by ascent and decline,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.46,0:57:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you have decided what kind of a charge to put on the little iron filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.28,0:57:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So your little iron filing, this is your spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.57,0:57:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got its karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.57,0:57:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're born, you can already calibrate a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.28,0:57:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute they're born, they have a calibrated level of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.21,0:57:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.50,0:57:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment of birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.61,0:57:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in a universe in which nothing is accidental,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.51,0:58:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then, the karmic propensity manifest in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.19,0:58:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,starts out at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.86,0:58:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, by your own will,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.94,0:58:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by your own will,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.23,0:58:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you, like, comfortably change the charge
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.44,0:58:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the polarity on this little iron filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.00,0:58:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where you go in this giant electromagnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.98,0:58:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is not up to an arbitrary god, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.76,0:58:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.84,0:58:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine justice is that what you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.30,0:58:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically aligns you in the field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.21,0:58:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.92,0:58:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which you are came about only by your own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.46,0:58:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one paddles his own canoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.15,0:58:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So there doesn't need to be an arbitrary god
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.78,0:58:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who gets jealous, angry, punitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.69,0:58:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.50,0:58:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically aligns you in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.59,0:58:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When the lightning bolt hits, it's not by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.40,0:58:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You just happen to be there and get fried,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.13,0:58:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's where you were in the electromagnetic spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.63,0:59:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, non-binding.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.26,0:59:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.78,0:59:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Participants are free to come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.53,0:59:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No proselytizing, no intimidating,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.78,0:59:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,no brainwashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.55,0:59:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.13,0:59:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People who work in this field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.13,0:59:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,do so voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.34,0:59:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Commonality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.19,0:59:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Recognition is a consequence of what one has become,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.84,0:59:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than as a result of ascribed titles, adjectives, or trappings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.65,0:59:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That gets you out of guruism.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.98,0:59:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Guruism, you know, calibrates now below 200, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.25,0:59:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of its exploitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.34,0:59:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In India.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.84,0:59:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,India has a tradition of exploitation, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.09,0:59:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the exploitation of the title, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.65,0:59:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it now calibrates below 200, that title,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.73,0:59:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which once was a very high title.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.61,1:00:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth avoids glamorization
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.09,1:00:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to impress people
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.40,1:00:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with wealth and great buildings
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.78,1:00:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and great trappings and drapings.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.38,1:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that's glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.44,1:00:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see in some, in a lot of cults,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.88,1:00:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the glamorization of spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.82,1:00:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the glamorization of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.01,1:00:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the seductive lure of the glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.42,1:00:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Every week we get some slick magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.65,1:00:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alleged to be spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.65,1:00:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,On the front, it's always slick.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.05,1:00:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's usually somebody in a meditating yoga position.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.05,1:00:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Failing that, there's a slick, seductive-looking,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.80,1:00:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty blonde or brunette, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.80,1:01:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole thing is done in a certain artistic style,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.92,1:01:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of like the 20s, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.17,1:01:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a glamorization and a seduction,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.53,1:01:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the adding of like a lure to it, a lure,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.88,1:01:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a seductive lure, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.07,1:01:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a big fair someplace next week,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.63,1:01:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these gurus and shamans
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.63,1:01:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.63,1:01:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.63,1:01:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And magic, magic is going to be very big.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.63,1:01:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.63,1:01:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a, you know, everyday kind of catalog.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.63,1:01:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.63,1:01:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The catalog I'm holding in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.63,1:01:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to cover it, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.63,1:01:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.46,1:01:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.46,1:01:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to spend the whole day
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.55,1:01:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in amusements.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.55,1:01:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These are okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.55,1:01:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you say I'm going to the New Age Festival Carnival,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.55,1:01:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.61,1:02:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is not to get seduced
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.09,1:02:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and trapped into it, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.09,1:02:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no teachers on the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.09,1:02:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who don't know what a teacher on this side knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.09,1:02:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard of a teacher on the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.17,1:02:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that couldn't tell you anything
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.17,1:02:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your grandmother couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.17,1:02:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, your mother-in-law, eat well,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.25,1:02:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, eat your spinach, watch your nutrition.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.25,1:02:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, are there adepts on the other side?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.59,1:02:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because they reach their highest level
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.59,1:02:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.59,1:02:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What we see is the New Age Festival
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.59,1:02:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is old hat in Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.59,1:02:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The same entities are still practicing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.59,1:02:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The same entities, they're on the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.69,1:02:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the astral domains.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.69,1:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Same entity that read your fortune
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.69,1:02:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in 450 BC is reading your fortune
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.38,1:02:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in Sedona next week.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.38,1:02:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Same entity, same entity.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.38,1:02:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so with a little kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.96,1:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can check it out for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.00,1:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If these people were spiritually erudite,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.00,1:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they would have transcended
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.00,1:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and be in heavenly realms by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.00,1:03:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Mesopotamia, you've had a lot of time, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.73,1:03:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To get off Energy 240,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.46,1:03:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be up to 500, 600 by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.46,1:03:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be in a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.46,1:03:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After a couple thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.46,1:03:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if this entity on the other side had it together,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.46,1:03:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they would have been in a celestial realm long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.46,1:03:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just find out with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.76,1:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the next time you get a reading.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.76,1:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How long that entity has been doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.76,1:03:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.92,1:03:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,After that much time, they are extremely adept.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.13,1:03:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They are extremely adept, and they're intuitive,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.13,1:03:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're very psychic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.13,1:03:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you go through that yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.82,1:03:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when the kundalini energy comes in.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.82,1:03:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know exactly what a person is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.82,1:03:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even see their past lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.82,1:03:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell by their aura, the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.82,1:03:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is an instant readout
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.82,1:03:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without even trying it, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.88,1:04:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So these people are very adept.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.88,1:04:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The slightest hesitation, they know they got you hooked.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.88,1:04:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People will say,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.88,1:04:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe that anymore, and I'm still going.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.88,1:04:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.44,1:04:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.73,1:04:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom to come and go.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.73,1:04:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Recognition of anybody with anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.13,1:04:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.13,1:04:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's inspirational.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.26,1:04:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.26,1:04:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No seduction.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.26,1:04:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-materialistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.26,1:04:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Neediness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.26,1:04:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to pump people for wealth,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.26,1:04:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,prestige, their connections,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.26,1:04:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,their buildings, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.26,1:04:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is already total and complete
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.69,1:04:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and has no need
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.69,1:04:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to proselytize
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.69,1:04:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or sign up people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.69,1:04:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to sign up people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.46,1:04:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.46,1:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,signing up anybody to come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.46,1:04:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if you've been signed up, I'm throwing out.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.46,1:04:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so much ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.53,1:04:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Give you ten bucks for everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.53,1:05:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to get there to sign up for.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.90,1:05:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.90,1:05:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's, you see, the commercialization of spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.90,1:05:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see commercialization of it all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.90,1:05:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.25,1:05:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no involvement,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.25,1:05:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,non-involvement in worldly affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.34,1:05:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not in any parades at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.34,1:05:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,These parades are too dangerous
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.50,1:05:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with the dogs
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.50,1:05:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fire hoses
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.61,1:05:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.15,1:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.63,1:05:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's non-involvement in worldly affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.63,1:05:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.63,1:05:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you see the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.63,1:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the evolution of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.92,1:05:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the convolutions
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.92,1:05:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which evolution goes through.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.92,1:05:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.94,1:05:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is identifiable
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.05,1:05:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,along a progressive gradient.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.05,1:05:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.05,1:05:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we mean
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.05,1:05:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.05,1:06:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it has no enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.05,1:06:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to castigate or oppose.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.05,1:06:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth would not be involved
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.13,1:06:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in a religious war.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.13,1:06:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth has nothing to gain
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.48,1:06:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by converts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.48,1:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.48,1:06:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So those who see converts
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.09,1:06:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are looking for worldly power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.09,1:06:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Worldly power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.15,1:06:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.15,1:06:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is transitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.15,1:06:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is a projected value
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.15,1:06:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.38,1:06:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-intentional.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.38,1:06:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth does not intervene
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.38,1:06:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or have any agenda or propose
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.38,1:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,on others.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.21,1:06:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't try to sell truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.21,1:06:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't try to impose it on others.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.21,1:06:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't try to glamorize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.21,1:06:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't commercialize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.67,1:06:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something within each person
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.67,1:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that hears the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.82,1:06:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're ready for it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.82,1:06:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you get it right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.82,1:07:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember somebody said
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.01,1:07:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was at some place
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.01,1:07:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he just mentioned
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.01,1:07:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody had ever heard of the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.01,1:07:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he said when you get home
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.01,1:07:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,look up the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.01,1:07:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.01,1:07:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When I got home I looked up the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.01,1:07:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I met the publisher
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.01,1:07:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,got to know Bill and Helen
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.01,1:07:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.01,1:07:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.01,1:07:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.19,1:07:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you're ready to hear it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.19,1:07:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you get it the first instant you hear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.51,1:07:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-intentional.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.51,1:07:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not intervene, have an agenda to propose
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.51,1:07:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't try to promulgate
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.51,1:07:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't try to enlist people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.51,1:07:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.86,1:07:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything occurs as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.86,1:07:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.90,1:07:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.90,1:07:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of something outside of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.78,1:07:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality manifests as actuality
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.78,1:07:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.78,1:07:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of causation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.78,1:07:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the minute you look for cause
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.78,1:07:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you're now involved in a
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.78,1:08:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,dualistic positionality with the world
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.78,1:08:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're going to favor this cause
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.78,1:08:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and defavor that cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.78,1:08:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This cause is going to become your enemy, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.65,1:08:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Tranquility and peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.65,1:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no issues or partialities.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.65,1:08:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No desire to change others
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.73,1:08:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or impose.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.18,1:08:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of higher energies
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.18,1:08:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is inside and not dependent
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.18,1:08:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on propagation or effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.18,1:08:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't need help anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.18,1:08:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than gravity needs
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.18,1:08:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the help of an apple falling from the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.89,1:08:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Does worship please God
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.89,1:08:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or does it just fulfill your own potentiality?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.89,1:08:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see God
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.89,1:08:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with his ego all puffed up
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.89,1:08:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,look at all the people worshiping him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.81,1:08:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.81,1:08:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.89,1:08:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality is the reverence for all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.89,1:08:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.35,1:08:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really avoids that which is deleterious
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.35,1:08:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than opposing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.35,1:09:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also in accord with Christ's teaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.35,1:09:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to oppose evil
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.35,1:09:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.35,1:09:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you perceive as evil
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.35,1:09:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,do not become interlocked with it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.35,1:09:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you will become
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.35,1:09:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at the effect of evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.35,1:09:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore hating evil and fighting evil
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.35,1:09:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is a losing cause
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.35,1:09:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because by doing so
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.35,1:09:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're merely propagated.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.80,1:09:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.80,1:09:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Reverence for all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.80,1:09:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.73,1:09:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to merely be benign
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.73,1:09:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to have good will towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.73,1:09:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People say
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.73,1:09:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what spiritual thing can I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.73,1:09:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I say just have good will towards all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.73,1:09:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what it may be
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.73,1:09:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and without exception.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.15,1:09:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This eventually leads to being conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.15,1:09:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and aware of the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.15,1:09:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This eventually
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.42,1:09:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,results in a reverence for all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.42,1:09:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.42,1:09:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this world and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.42,1:10:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.40,1:10:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk around the beetle
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.40,1:10:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of stepping on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.40,1:10:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go to great lengths
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.40,1:10:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.63,1:10:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,scrupulosity but
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.81,1:10:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you see people at a certain level
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.03,1:10:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched a guy actually
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.03,1:10:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,go out of his way and
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.14,1:10:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,risk turning his car over
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.14,1:10:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to try and hit a cat that was
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.14,1:10:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,crossing the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.14,1:10:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned on his wheels, went up on two wheels
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.14,1:10:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,he was trying to hit this cat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.55,1:10:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is different than stepping over the beetle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.55,1:10:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've used the beetle many times.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.55,1:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The beetle lays there
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and his little legs are going like this
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.68,1:10:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and above consciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.68,1:10:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you grab a twig and you put it down
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.68,1:10:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he grabs it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.68,1:10:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he walks away. He's happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.68,1:10:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that may not
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.57,1:10:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,do him any good but it's good for your karma
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.57,1:10:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.57,1:10:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell did you turn me over
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.64,1:10:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on my feet for? I was having a good time
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.64,1:10:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,laying on my back wiggling my feet
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.64,1:11:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,this idiot comes over and grabs me
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.64,1:11:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.85,1:11:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because eventually you see
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.85,1:11:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.85,1:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So if evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.27,1:11:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and creation are one
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.27,1:11:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.43,1:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then what you eventually begin to witness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.43,1:11:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sacredness of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.43,1:11:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have a reverence
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.47,1:11:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.50,1:11:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you care
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.32,1:11:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for everything equally.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.81,1:11:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.89,1:11:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,care for the beautiful flower
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.89,1:11:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's nicer than this
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.89,1:11:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,nor am I
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.15,1:11:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,going to waste this.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.38,1:11:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know everything
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.38,1:11:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what a wonderful
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.38,1:11:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how we're surrounded by
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.38,1:11:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing but wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.38,1:11:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.53,1:11:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,life is realized to be eternal
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.53,1:11:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and physicality is temporary
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.56,1:12:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,life is not subject to death
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.56,1:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that brings us to the law
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.56,1:12:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.46,1:12:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,conservation of matter
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.46,1:12:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,conservation of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.46,1:12:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of conservation of life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.46,1:12:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,life cannot be destroyed
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.02,1:12:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it can only be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.02,1:12:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,forced to change form
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.42,1:12:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when you spot the moth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.42,1:12:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,slap the moth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.51,1:12:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he goes right on flying
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.51,1:12:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in his etheric body
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.76,1:12:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't even notice it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.30,1:12:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you think he died
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.42,1:12:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how could he die
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.42,1:12:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,death is not a possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.42,1:12:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the moth goes right on flying
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.52,1:12:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in his etheric body
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.64,1:12:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't even notice
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.64,1:12:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.64,1:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because his energy body
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.64,1:12:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is what he experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.64,1:12:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.26,1:12:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's only experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.26,1:13:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,his own experience to begin with
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.63,1:13:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.30,1:13:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.22,1:13:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is not provable
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.19,1:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is provable
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.19,1:13:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is linear
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.23,1:13:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and within the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.23,1:13:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,instead it's mystical
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.85,1:13:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it arises as
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.31,1:13:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.31,1:13:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ineffable
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.89,1:13:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,not capable of definition
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.97,1:13:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of temporality
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.97,1:13:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the end 26?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.97,1:13:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we have 31
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.03,1:14:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,38 oh my god you've been sneaking some more in
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.03,1:14:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,affirmative
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.06,1:14:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,non-operative
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.47,1:14:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,truth does not do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.47,1:14:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it just is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.34,1:14:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it influences everything around it
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.34,1:14:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that which it is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.34,1:14:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,not by virtue of that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.34,1:14:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which it does
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.34,1:14:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is looking at it from causality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.34,1:14:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.53,1:14:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks that it's because of what
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.53,1:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the person does
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.56,1:14:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no, it's because of what the person is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.56,1:14:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,their presence transforms
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.56,1:14:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy in the room
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.56,1:14:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,non-predictive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.81,1:14:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it doesn't predict
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.81,1:14:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the events in the future
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.81,1:14:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the world is going to end in 1692
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.81,1:14:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever it's going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.92,1:14:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,non-sentimental
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.97,1:14:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of emotionality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.30,1:14:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so sometimes I sound cryptic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.30,1:14:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because emotionality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.35,1:14:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalism
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.35,1:14:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is a self-indulgence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.68,1:14:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a self-indulgence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.13,1:15:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he died
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.13,1:15:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,right, right
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.60,1:15:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.30,1:15:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is anything more necessary?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.64,1:15:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,no, nothing more is necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.64,1:15:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the message
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.26,1:15:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've gone through the death of many people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.26,1:15:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,close friends
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.89,1:15:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I got he's gone
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.89,1:15:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,period
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.11,1:15:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the end of it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.18,1:15:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the hurricane killed 3000 people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.18,1:15:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.56,1:15:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,save the emotionality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.43,1:15:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.43,1:15:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're bleeding out energy all over the place
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.43,1:15:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody is helped by your emotionality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.22,1:15:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody needs a fracture fixed
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.22,1:15:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're crying and blubbering
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.22,1:15:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,how much?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.73,1:15:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you need the cast put on
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.73,1:15:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you need something to eat
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.18,1:15:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,non-emotionally
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.18,1:15:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so it doesn't get sentimental
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.18,1:15:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and waste energy on emotionalism
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.18,1:16:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,non-authoritarian
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.18,1:16:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no rules or dictates to be followed
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.18,1:16:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,non-egoistic
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.18,1:16:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers respected only for
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.18,1:16:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what they are
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.18,1:16:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what they have become
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.60,1:16:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,educational provides information in every kind of format
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.60,1:16:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you can think of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.78,1:16:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,books, audio tapes, video tapes, lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.78,1:16:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,self-supporting
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.78,1:16:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,neither mercenary nor materialistic
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.78,1:16:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't solicit
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.94,1:16:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,freestanding
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.56,1:16:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,complete without dependence on external
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.56,1:16:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.93,1:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what I say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.22,1:16:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,depends completely
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.22,1:16:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.26,1:16:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not so
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.86,1:16:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because so and so said it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.86,1:16:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the year 720
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.15,1:16:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so because it's so
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.15,1:16:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,right now
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.15,1:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because truth is always true
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.82,1:16:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,like right now
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.82,1:16:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so instead of quoting authorities
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.52,1:16:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so and so
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.52,1:17:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you shine forth the truth of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.52,1:17:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,period
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.61,1:17:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so you are your own authority
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.61,1:17:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the self within is the authority
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.02,1:17:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not so
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.02,1:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm the sixth descendant
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.02,1:17:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sixteenth patriarch
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.02,1:17:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.67,1:17:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is putting
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.69,1:17:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of truth outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.69,1:17:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.73,1:17:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the mystic knows it's a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.73,1:17:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the radiance, the effulgence of the self
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.73,1:17:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.82,1:17:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because the truth is just obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.82,1:17:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to quote from somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.82,1:17:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just plain obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.82,1:17:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's stunningly obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.82,1:17:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd have to be a noodle-heimer not to see it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.82,1:17:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,freestanding
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.82,1:17:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,complete without dependence on external
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.82,1:17:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.11,1:17:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you might have induced
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.11,1:17:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, natural, and I think that's the last one
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.34,1:17:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of altered states of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.34,1:17:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.85,1:17:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,my understanding and my experience
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.88,1:17:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not to try to force the kundalini
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.88,1:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,energy up
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.44,1:18:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,why? because the kundalini energy will rise
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.44,1:18:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,through the chakra system as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.44,1:18:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you have become
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.53,1:18:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,when you become forgiving towards others
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.53,1:18:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.53,1:18:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and beauty of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.53,1:18:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.25,1:18:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,flows in accordance with it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.25,1:18:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so artificial means
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.81,1:18:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of trying to raise the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.81,1:18:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,through various systems
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.92,1:18:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think is unwise
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.92,1:18:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's premature
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.92,1:18:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could handle the energy at that level
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.92,1:18:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be at that level
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.02,1:18:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so people get into weird and strange
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.02,1:18:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual crises
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.34,1:18:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from trying to force
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.34,1:18:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy systems
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.34,1:18:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with breathing systems
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.34,1:18:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and various yoga systems
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.34,1:18:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,all of which have their place
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.34,1:18:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're in accord
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.65,1:18:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which you have
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.65,1:18:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,really become
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.72,1:18:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.39,1:18:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the best known example of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.39,1:19:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,misplaced
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.39,1:19:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,practices such as that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.81,1:19:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,such as that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.26,1:19:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it was Gopi Krishna
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.26,1:19:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Gopi Krishna wrote a book about it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.26,1:19:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,one of Gopi Krishna's
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.26,1:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,friends has been in many of our lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.26,1:19:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.31,1:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Gopi Krishna's kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.31,1:19:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,went up one side of the brain
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.31,1:19:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was lopsided and had a terrible time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.31,1:19:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for some years
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.31,1:19:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as the kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.31,1:19:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to rise
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.31,1:19:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.51,1:19:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like an exquisite pleasure
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.51,1:19:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,flowing up your back
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.51,1:19:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you feel it flowing into your brain
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.51,1:19:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if you close your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.51,1:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you go into a bliss state all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.51,1:19:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody complains
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.51,1:19:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,why you've always got your eyes closed
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.51,1:19:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because that bliss state is there
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.51,1:19:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy comes up
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.51,1:19:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and with it it occasions
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.51,1:19:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of the so called
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.77,1:19:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,SIDDHIS
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.77,1:19:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which again should not be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.77,1:19:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,pursued for their own sake
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.77,1:19:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so the last spiritual trap
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.77,1:20:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll mention
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.82,1:20:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the pursuit of the so called
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.82,1:20:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,cities for their own sake
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.82,1:20:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,taking classes on
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.82,1:20:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.93,1:20:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,occurring natural phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.93,1:20:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,once that kundalini
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.93,1:20:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,rises all those so called
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.93,1:20:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,super normal phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.93,1:20:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,arise and happen of their own
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.93,1:20:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and to try to acquire
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.09,1:20:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,them
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.25,1:20:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're going to take a class on levitation
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.25,1:20:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,good luck
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.81,1:20:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.19,1:20:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that the attraction
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.19,1:20:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to take a course in one of these cities
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.19,1:20:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is already an ego vanity
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.19,1:20:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise you wouldn't be wanting to take it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.19,1:20:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.19,1:20:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unless it's something you've already experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.19,1:20:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just want to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.26,1:20:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,learn and discipline it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.32,1:20:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so what happens now
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.32,1:20:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is we're going to have Niko chat
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.32,1:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.32,1:20:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we shared the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.32,1:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,heart of man
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.32,1:21:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and now Niko is going to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.32,1:21:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,do the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.57,1:21:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,chant
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.57,1:21:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Sutra in Sanskrit
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.57,1:21:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which again is experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.57,1:21:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,after the chant then
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.76,1:21:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll reassemble for questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.76,1:21:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.07,1:21:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take this out
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.68,1:21:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,do the chairs support you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.68,1:21:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,any issues
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.77,1:22:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,no
